Study Population: New York State residents aged 18 and over.

Data Source: Empire State Poll (ESP) 2019, a random-digit-dial telephone survey conducted by the Survey Research from February to April in 2019 that covers 800 completed interviews. 400 (50%) of the participants were from downstate and the rest were from upstate. Study Variables

  1. Outcomes

  • JAq4 - self-reported health status

    • 1 = Excellent
    • 2 = Very Good
    • 3 = Good
    • 4 = Fair
    • 5 = Poor

  • RVq2 - visits to care providers in the past 12 months

    • 1 = Never
    • 2 = 1-2 times
    • 3 = Once every few months
    • 4 = Once a month
    • 5 = Twice a month
    • 6 = Once a week
    • 7 = 2-3 times a week
  1. Predictors

  • SNS-3: 3-item version of the Subjective Numeracy Scale (SNS), which was validated having good internal reliability and correlated highly with the full SNS.

    • JAq1 - rate competence related to fractions (1 = not good at all to 6 = extremely good)
    • JAq2 - rate competence related to percentages (1 = not good at all to 6 = extremely good)
    • JAq3 - rate usefulness related to numerical information (1 = never to 6 = very often)
  1. Covariates

  • Demographical variables

    • gender 1=Male, 2=Female, 3=Other, -1=Refused
    • age 18-20, 21-44, 45-64, 65+, -1=Refused
    • educ 1-3=High school or less, 4-5=Some college or associates degree, 6-7=Bachelors degree or higher, -1=Refused
    • hhince household income in 2018 before taxes ($): 1-5=<50k, 6-7=50k-100k, 8=100k-150k, 9=150k+, NA=No Data
    • race White, Black, Natam, Asian, Other, More than 1 race, -1=Refused
    • hisp ethnicity: 0=Non-Hispanic, 1=Hispanic, -1=Refused

Distribution of Health Score: the distribution of self-stated health status is right skewed. The median is 3 (Good) and more than 75% of the interviewees had health status equal to or better than Good.

Distribution of Care Provider Visits: the distribution of care provider visits is right skewed. The median is 3 (Once every few months) and more than 75% of the interviewees had the visit frequency equal to or less than Once every few months.

Distribution of the Combination of Care Provider Visits and Health Status

The heatmap shows that the top 4 cells of care provider visits and health status are: (Once every few months, Good), (Once every few moths, Very Good), (1-2 times, Good) and (1-2 times, Very Good), which is consistent with the previous results of the distribution of health status or care provider visits alone.

Horizontally reading the plot, we infer that people with excellent health status tend to have lower frequency than the other groups, and that people under poor health condition will visit care providers more than others. However, especially for the poor group, we are not 100% confident to draw such a conclusion since the number of interviewees involved in this subgroup was limited.

On the other hand, based on the distribution of health status in each subgroup of visits, there is no obvious difference among the first 6 groups but only people who visit care providers the most frequently (2-3 times a week) are more likely to have not good health condition.

Data Processing for Regression

Discussion about Refusal Rate and Missing Values

  • Refusal rate: the refusal rate of race and age are higher than the other variables. For further analysis, we will keep the missing values of race, ethnicity and gender and otherwise drop those of others.

  • Missing values: for further analysis, we will keep the missing values of race, ethnicity and gender and otherwise drop those of others.

JAq1: How good are you at working with fractions?
JAq2: How good are you at figuring out how much a shirt will cost if it is 25% off?
JAq3: How often do you find numerical information to be useful?

Calculation of Numeracy Score

For further analysis (regression), the sum of JAq1, JAq2 and JAq3 will serve as the predictor of the model. Though almost all the answers were with positive value, which we would like to call as correct answers, there were a few incorrect answers with value -1=Refused and -2=Dont know.

2 participants had more than half (2) wrong answers, so they were dropped from the dataset. 11 had only 1 wrong answer and the these negative values will be imputated using the average score of all the other correct answers across each SNS item 4.74.

Finally 798 participants were kept and we got the final predictor numeracy.

Demographical Comparison Table: New York State vs.ESP

This comparison is aimed to compare the the sample distribution of ESP with the population of New York State (NYS). All the data of NYS was found in the tables United States Census Bureau. Since the data of each demographical characteristics was collected from different tables, the total numbers (in thousand)were close but may be not equal to each other.

Apart from dropping some missing values, we collapsed the levels of race into 3: White, Black and Other.

We performed Fishers test to evaluate the difference between ESP sample and NYS population. The p-value less than 0.05 indicates that it is worth considering to add weight (the proportion of each subgroup in NYS) into the regression model.

Based on the table below, we find that:

  • There is no significant difference in gender, age and ethnicity.
  • There is significant difference in education, income and race.
    • People with higher education / income level tend to have higher will to be interviewed.
    • Among the participants, the proportion of white people were closed to that in NYS. The reason why there were significant difference was ESP had lower proportion of black people involved than the group other than white and black.
